# The Rout of the Talosians

## Scene summary (from gm-assist, verbatim)

#### Brewbarry cuts down the anchorite and several orcs while Vukradin continues his preaching, breaking the warband's morale.
- With the anchorite dead, orcs 1, 4, 5, and 8 flee the battlefield entirely.
- Orc 3, after taking a swing at Vukradin (which is Silver Barbed and forced to reroll — missing), also flees. Vukradin opts not to use his attack of opportunity, instead calling out "See the way to Lathander!" as the orc runs.
- Orc 6 (receptive), seeing all his companions flee and the bright light of Valphine's power on display, decides life is too short and runs.
- Orc 7 was killed earlier by Brewbarry's attack of opportunity.
- Orc 9 is killed by Brewbarry. Orc 10 is knocked unconscious. Orc 11 flees.
- The DM discusses the poor optics of the party's religious outreach: a Drow cleric, an undead horse, and a Dwarf covered in blood present a confusing spectacle. "I have to say the performance was not the best organized religious ceremony," the DM observes. "This is why religious figures wear masks all the time," Vukradin's player replies.
- The unconscious orc 10 is briefly considered for conversion; the party jokes about waking him with "a glorious sunlight sacrament."

## Verbatim moments

**[Orc 1 Flees After the Anchorite's Death]**
- Orc 1 is declared receptive; seeing companions flee and the bright display of power, he tosses a javelin at Boney (finding him an abomination) then flees the battlefield.
- Brewbarry is offered an attack of opportunity as Orc 1 flees.

**[GM]** — *explaining Orc 1's behaviour*
> "So he's going to… Tosses Javelin… at… Boney, because he finds him an abomination."

**[GM]** — *offering the reaction opportunity*
> "Gary, you do have a reaction opportunity against number one, as he flees."

**[Gary Young / Brewbarry]** — *deciding whether to strike*
> "Against number one."

**[GM]** — *confirming*
> "Yes, Brewbarry can use his reaction if he so chooses."

**[Gary Young / Brewbarry]** — *in character for Brewbarry*
> "Beat down the heathens? Yeah."
> "Yeah, okay, yeah, that's in character for Brewbarry."

**[GM]** — *rolling the attack*
> "Alright, he misses. Bye. This guy runs off the."

**[David Mendenhall / Vukradin]** — *reacting in character*
> "Brewbarry, I said, don't attack!"
> "Well, but you missed on purpose, right?"

**[Gary Young / Brewbarry]** — *clarifying the intent*
> "On purpose. He's just intimidating them."

**[GM]** — *narrating Brewbarry's purpose*
> "Just to remind them that, you know, who's in charge, who's got the violence, who can do the stick."

---

**[Orc 3's Attack, Silver Barbs, and Flight]**
- Orc 3 swings at Vukradin; Vukradin casts Silvery Barbs, forcing a reroll.

**[GM]** — *declaring Orc 3's action*
> "3 is going to… Charge here… And attack… the bard."
> "Because the bard's between… because they can't reach the cleric, that's why. And Brewbarry looks kind of scary."

**[GM]** — *on the reroll after Silvery Barbs*
> "Rolled a 9."

**[David Mendenhall / Vukradin]** — *confirming the miss*
> "You get a 9, so you miss?"

**[GM]**
> "Yes."

**[David Mendenhall / Vukradin]** — *on the Silvery Barbs spell slot triggering Universal Speak*
> "Alright, excellent. And since I cast a spell. That means I, on my next turn, will have another use of Universal Speak. Which I look forward to using."

**[GM]** — *after the miss, Orc 3 flees*
> "And he flees."
> "You can give an attack of opportunity if you want."

**[GM]** — *identifying who gets the opportunity*
> "Number 3."

**[David Mendenhall / Vukradin]** — *choosing not to attack, calling out instead*
> "No, I'm not attacking, I'm like, dude, don't leave!"
> "See the way to… to Lathander!"

**[GM]** — *narrating the orc's mindset as he runs*
> "they're kind of like, you know, this is who we are. You know, you killed our big boss, you've shown your power of your God, and, you know, I tried to hit you, and I had this masterful hit, and it kind of missed. At this point in time, I'm kind of like, you know what, this just doesn't feel like the right… this does not feel like the right situation for me."

