**[The DM's Commentary on the Party's Poor Religious Spectacle]**

**[David Mendenhall / Vukradin]** — *suggesting a song might help*
> "Can't… Maybe I should play a song or something. Maybe that would persuade."

**[GM]** — *diagnosing the problem*
> "Well, maybe if Valphine hadn't gone around screaming."

**[David Mendenhall / Vukradin]**
> "Yeah, that probably didn't help."
> "To the death metal, Valphine."

**[GM]** — *continuing the diagnosis*
> "And maybe if, you know, you weren't running around with an undead horse."

**[Wade Brown / Soma]**
> "What undead horse, we got out of the way."

**[GM]**
> "I'm just saying, like, you know, there… there's some dynamics here that are causing confusion, right? The drow cleric with the light and the undead is kind of cause…"

**[David Mendenhall / Vukradin]**
> "You're telling us we need to work on our… on our showmanship here."

**[GM]**
> "Yes, I'm…"

**[David Mendenhall / Vukradin]**
> "We gotta work on the spectacle a bit."

**[GM]**
> "I have to say the performance… yeah, I just gotta give her credit, gotta give her credit, you know?"

**[David Mendenhall / Vukradin]**
> "This is why religious figures wear masks all the time."

**[GM]**
> "Yeah, there's a… there's a reason why there's ceremonies… Structure."
> "I'm just saying, this was not the best organized religious ceremony."

**[David Mendenhall / Vukradin]**
> "Good attempt, though, it was a good attempt."

